  "body": "### What\r\n\r\nRemove Stack too Deep errors as blockers to via IR and making them less annoying to users.\r\n\r\n### Why\r\n\r\nCurrently, the via-IR compilation pipeline is not viable as default compilation mode for two reasons:\r\n- Without optimizer hardly any non-trivial project compiles due to stack-too-deep errors.\r\n- Even with optimizer, some more complex projects suffer from stack-too-deep errors.\r\n\r\n\r\n### How\r\n\r\nProducing better error messages in remaining error cases. (allowing devs to fix them more easily)\r\n\r\nCase 1: EOF has immediate swaps dups:\r\n  - use them\r\nCase 2 (otherwise):\r\n   Rewrite the optimized evm code transform to act on Yul ASTs instead of CFGs resulting in more precise predictions of the effects of the stack-to-memory mover, resulting in the ability to precisely move those variables that will avoid stack too deep errors.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n\r\n### Out of scope\r\n\r\n- Avoiding stack too deep errors:\r\n  -  under all circumstances: Like in recursive functions.\r\n  - in the presence of memory unsafe assembly \r\n\r\n---\r\n### Resources\r\n\r\n1. Design doc\r\n",
